data.title: Abutilon hulseanum (Torr. & A.Gray) Torr. ex Baker f.
data.meta_description: The native range of this species is S. Central U.S.A. to Central America, Florida to Caribbean. It is a shrub and grows primarily in the seasonally dry tropical biome.
